National Association of Nigerian Students (NANS) has urged both federal and state governments to expedite action on reopening of schools for academic activities, saying the continued closure ofschools would have negative impact on the students. The leadership of the association also warned those parading themselves as NANS officials and issuing fake statements purportedly on behalf of the student body to desist from the act. NANS spoke yesterday, in a statement signed by its officials, including Kowe Odunayo Amos Coordinator, NANS Zone D; Akinteye  Babatunde , Chairman, NANS, Joint Campus Committee (JCC) Ondo axis; Bamgbose Tomiwa Chairman, NANS, JCC Ogun axis;  Busari AbdulQowiyy, Chairman, NANS JCC Lagos Axis; Agbogunleri Seun, Chairman, NANS JCC Osun Axis and Fadare Blessing, Chairman, NANS, JCC Oyo Axis. NANS said the major interest of the vast majority of Nigerian students is to have schools re-opened.  